  "datePublished": "2025-12-31",
  "description": "A quasi-category is a [simplicial set](./simplicial-set.md) in which every inner [horn](./horn.md) has a filler: for every map Λⁿₖ → X with 0 \u003c k \u003c n, there exists an extension Δⁿ → X. This condition ensures that composites of [morphisms](../../ordinary-categories/terms/morphism.md) exist but are not required to be unique — they are unique only up to a contractible space of choices.",
